target_title: Explicitly call adw_init()

note.body:
Libadwaita maintainer here.

> GTK 4.17.0 added an assertion that fails if gtk_init() has not been called prior to accessing the default display. Initial Setup triggers this assertion because of the call to adw_style_manager_get_default() later in main(), added in the same commit, after constructing the GisDriver (subclass of AdwApplication):

You should change this. Calling `adw_style_manager_get_default()` before `adw_init()` is, and has always been, undefined behavior. The correct place to set color scheme from when using `AdwApplication` is `startup()`. You shouldn't need a manual `adw_init()` call.

Libadwaita docs don't mention this, because they assume that you know how `gtk_init()` behaves in GtkApplication and basically treats `adw_init()` the same way. Perhaps it should.
